data.current_description: Retrieve valid classifications to use when creating a support case. Classifications are hierarchical. Each classification is a string containing all levels of the hierarchy separated by `" > "`. For example, `"Technical Issue > Compute > Compute Engine"`. Classification IDs returned by this endpoint are valid for at least six months. When a classification is deactivated, this endpoint immediately stops returning it. After six months, `case.create` requests using the classification will fail. EXAMPLES: cURL: ```shell curl \ --header "Authorization: Bearer $(gcloud auth print-access-token)" \ 'https://cloudsupport.googleapis.com/v2/caseClassifications:search?query=display_name:"*Compute%20Engine*"' ``` Python: ```python import googleapiclient.discovery supportApiService = googleapiclient.discovery.build( serviceName="cloudsupport", version="v2", discoveryServiceUrl=f"https://cloudsupport.googleapis.com/$discovery/rest?version=v2", ) request = supportApiService.caseClassifications().search( query='display_name:"*Compute Engine*"' ) print(request.execute()) ```
data.summary_suggestion: Search for valid case classifications by query
data.description_suggestion: Search for valid case classifications to use when creating a support case. Accepts a query parameter to filter classifications by display name or other attributes. Returns a hierarchical list of classifications formatted as strings with levels separated by " > " (e.g., "Technical Issue > Compute > Compute Engine"). Classification IDs are valid for at least six months; deactivated classifications are immediately excluded from results, and expired classifications will cause case.create requests to fail.
data.reasoning: Missing summary entirely. Description is lengthy and includes examples but lacks clarity on input parameters (query format) and output structure. Improved summary is action-oriented and concise. Enhanced description clarifies the query parameter usage, output format, and validity period of returned classifications for better AI agent understanding.
